TY  - JOUR
AB  - The data in Fehr and Tyran (2001) and Petersen and Winn (2014) show that money illusion plays an important role in nominal price adjustment after a fully anticipated negative monetary shock. Money illusion affects subjects' expectations, and causes pronounced nominal inertia after a negative shock but much less inertia after a positive shock Thus Petersen and Winn (2014) provide a misleading interpretation of both our and their own data.
